<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-32-0280 </DOCNO><TEXT>Automatic exposure control systems are intended to guarantee in dailyroutines an optimum and constant film blackening or optical density.The paper first describes the design and functions of automatic exposurecontrol units as far as necessary for understanding the quality controlmethods discussed. The various testing procedures for approval tests,quality tests and constancy tests are briefly dealt with, followed bya brief discussion of the problem of mean optical density in the dominantrange.</TEXT></DOC>